<br>
Only one thing ya missed with respect to manaburn's downside... it really limits VI's options for future encounters.  Since it's not resistable, there simply can't be any worthwhile single group encounter mobs that have less than about 6x average manaburn hp, or the encounter is probably trivial before it's even introduced.  Same deal with raid mobs, only on a bigger scale.<br>
<br>
I dunno about others, but with fights lasting 20-30 minutes occasionally, it does seem a lot more... satisfying? than the old 1-2 min fights were you either won or CRed.  It allows flavor to be added (repop control, positioning, non-stupid effects (i.e. not DT) to otherwise cookiecutter fights... a good thing.  Clearing in for a half hour or so to a fight that was over in a minute (one way or the other) always seemed kinda lame to me.<br>
<br>
That's pretty much my only complaint about MB, otherwise I think it's a pretty cool skill.  Might make sense to make it have a non-stacking 1pt dot effect (or similar) tho, to keep massed MBs from being a problem.  You could still burn a mob, but not everybody at once... pvp thing is pretty messed up too, but at least forlorn totems cast faster than MB does. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
